cs.LG, cs.CE, cs.AI, cs.DB, cs.NE 

This paper involves building and evaluating various machine learning models to predict one-year mortality in patients diagnosed with acute myocardial infarction or post myocardial infarction syndrome. Therefore, the most likely arXiv CS sub-category is cs.LG (Machine Learning). Other likely sub-categories include cs.CE (Computational Engineering, Finance, and Science), cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence), cs.DB (Databases), and cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) as these sub-categories are also relevant to the study's focus on machine learning and prediction models.
